'''Vjatšeslav Leedo''' (born 1952) is the [[stockholder]]{{clarify|date=May 2017|reason="The stockholder" is extremely vague. Is he the sole shareholder? Or at least the majority shareholder? Please specify.}} of [[Saaremaa Shipping Company]], and due to a number of controversial remarks, commonly recognised as the 'face' of the company.  Particularly known are his frequently voiced opposition towards building a bridge between [[Virtsu]] and [[Kuivastu]], a transit route currently served by Saaremaa Shipping Company, and yearly allegations{{Citation needed|date=May 2017}} regarding his orders, supposedly deliberately too early, to begin [[ice breaking]] on the route.  This procedure breaks the [[ice road]] between [[Virtsu]] and [[Kuivastu]].  The ice road is free to use for everybody, but when it's broken, transit must be done by ferry service, and this profits Saaremaa Shipping Company.

